# Stratum Classifier (INV-QUERY-005, INV-QUERY-006)

## Task
Implement the 6-strata classification system for Datalog queries.

## Six Strata (spec/03-query.md §3.5–3.7)
- S0: Ground queries — no variables, lookup only
- S1: Monotone — positive body atoms only, CALM-compliant
- S2: Stratified negation — negation allowed, requires stratification
- S3: Aggregation — aggregation operators (count, sum, max, min)
- S4: Recursive aggregation — fixpoint with aggregation
- S5: Full Datalog — unrestricted (may not terminate)

## Stage 0 Evaluation (INV-QUERY-006)
Stage 0 evaluates S0 and S1 ONLY. S2+ queries are CLASSIFIED but REJECTED at evaluation time.
The classifier must exist for all 6 strata even though only 2 evaluate.

## Classification Algorithm
```rust
pub fn classify_query(rules: &[Rule]) -> Stratum {
    if rules.iter().all(|r| r.body.is_empty()) { return Stratum::S0; }
    if rules.iter().all(|r| r.body.iter().all(|a| !a.is_negated())) {
        if rules.iter().all(|r| !r.is_recursive()) { return Stratum::S1; }
        // S1 includes monotone recursion
        return Stratum::S1;
    }
    if can_stratify(rules) {
        if has_aggregation(rules) {
            if has_recursive_aggregation(rules) { return Stratum::S4; }
            return Stratum::S3;
        }
        return Stratum::S2;
    }
    Stratum::S5
}
```

## CALM Compliance (INV-QUERY-007)
S0 and S1 queries are monotone → can run without coordination.
This is verified: if stratum <= S1, the query is CALM-compliant.

## Types
```rust
pub enum Stratum { S0, S1, S2, S3, S4, S5 }

impl Stratum {
    pub fn is_evaluable_stage0(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Stratum::S0 | Stratum::S1)
    }
    pub fn is_monotone(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Stratum::S0 | Stratum::S1)
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 6 strata defined
- [ ] Classifier correctly categorizes test queries for each stratum
- [ ] S0/S1 queries accepted for evaluation
- [ ] S2+ queries classified but rejected with clear error
- [ ] CALM compliance check: S0/S1 → true, S2+ → false
- [ ] proptest: classification is deterministic

## Traces To
spec/03-query.md §3.5–3.7, guide/03-query.md §3.2, INV-QUERY-005–007

