Per INV-HARVEST-007, harvest should issue proactive warnings before context loss:

  pub fn check_proactive_warnings(session: &SessionState) -> Vec<HarvestWarning> {
      let mut warnings = Vec::new();

      // Warning 1: Turn count approaching harvest threshold
      if session.turn_count >= 20 {
          warnings.push(HarvestWarning::ApproachingHarvestThreshold {
              current_turns: session.turn_count,
              threshold: 25,
              message: 'Consider running harvest soon (20/25 turns used)',
          });
      }

      // Warning 2: Methodology score declining
      if session.methodology_score < 0.5 {
          warnings.push(HarvestWarning::MethodologyDecline {
              m_t: session.methodology_score,
              message: 'M(t) below 0.5 — harvest recommended to capture session state',
          });
      }

      // Warning 3: Pending gaps accumulating
      if session.pending_harvest.len() > 5 {
          warnings.push(HarvestWarning::PendingGapsAccumulating {
              count: session.pending_harvest.len(),
              message: format!('{} epistemic gaps pending — harvest to persist', session.pending_harvest.len()),
          });
      }

      warnings
  }

  pub enum HarvestWarning {
      ApproachingHarvestThreshold { current_turns: usize, threshold: usize, message: &'static str },
      MethodologyDecline { m_t: f64, message: &'static str },
      PendingGapsAccumulating { count: usize, message: String },
  }

Q(t) PROXY (turn-count based): At Stage 0, Q(t) is approximated by:
  Q_proxy(t) = 1.0 - (turn_count / 25.0).min(1.0)
  This decreases linearly from 1.0 (fresh session) to 0.0 (25 turns).
  Stage 1+ replaces this with the full Q(t) multi-signal computation.

V:TYPE — check_proactive_warnings compiles
V:PROP — no warnings at turn 0 with M(t) = 1.0
V:PROP — always warns at turn 25

