# ASSOCIATE → ASSEMBLE → COMPRESS Pipeline

## ASSOCIATE (INV-SEED-003)
Build relevance graph from store entities:
```rust
pub fn associate(store: &Store, context: &SessionContext) -> RelevanceGraph {
    // 1. Query store for entities related to current task
    // 2. Weight edges by: recency, access frequency, dependency distance
    // 3. Bounded: terminates in O(E * k) where E = entities, k = max neighbors
}
```

## ASSEMBLE (INV-SEED-001, INV-SEED-005, INV-SEED-006)
Select top-K entities, render as five-part template:
```rust
pub struct SeedAssembly {
    pub context: String,         // project context (intention anchoring)
    pub invariants: String,      // governing INVs
    pub decisions: String,       // recent ADRs
    pub risks: String,           // uncertainty markers
    pub demonstrations: String,  // worked examples
}
```

## COMPRESS (INV-SEED-002, INV-SEED-004)
Budget-aware compression:
```rust
pub fn compress(assembly: SeedAssembly, budget_tokens: usize) -> String {
    let mut sections = assembly.to_priority_sorted_sections();
    while estimate_tokens(&sections) > budget_tokens {
        // Compress lowest-priority section
        sections.last_mut().unwrap().compress();
    }
    render(sections)
}
```

Token estimation: chars / 4 approximation (ADR-BUDGET-004).

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] ASSOCIATE builds relevance graph and terminates in bounded time
- [ ] ASSEMBLE produces five-part template with intention anchoring
- [ ] COMPRESS respects token budget
- [ ] Lower-priority sections compressed before higher
- [ ] Demonstration density proportional to uncertainty
- [ ] Seed is deterministic projection of store state
- [ ] proptest: budget_compliance (output <= budget for all inputs)

## Traces To
spec/06-seed.md §6.1-6.7, guide/06-seed.md

