# Kani Bounded Proof Harnesses (spec/16-verification.md §16.4)

## Task
Implement 48 Kani proof harnesses covering core invariants.

## Kani Tiers (guide/10-verification.md §10.3)
- Fast tier (PRs): 14 harnesses, ~30s total
- Full tier (nightly): 34 harnesses, ~5min
- Extended tier (weekly): 48 harnesses, ~30min

## Fast Tier Harnesses (14)
```rust
#[cfg(kani)]
mod proofs {
    use super::*;

    #[kani::proof]
    fn store_monotonic_growth() {
        let store = Store::genesis();
        let datom: Datom = kani::any();
        let store2 = store.with_datom(datom);
        assert!(store2.len() >= store.len());
    }

    #[kani::proof]
    fn datom_content_identity() {
        let d1: Datom = kani::any();
        let d2: Datom = kani::any();
        kani::assume(d1.entity == d2.entity && d1.attribute == d2.attribute
            && d1.value == d2.value && d1.tx == d2.tx && d1.op == d2.op);
        assert_eq!(d1, d2); // Content identity (C2)
    }

    #[kani::proof]
    fn merge_commutativity() {
        let s1: Store = kani::any();
        let s2: Store = kani::any();
        assert_eq!(s1.merge(&s2), s2.merge(&s1));
    }

    // ... 11 more for fast tier
}
```

