[AUDIT-R3 MEDIUM FIX] Comonad classification precision.

The Guidance comonad is the ENV COMONAD, which is the simplest comonadic structure.
This is NOT aspirational category theory — it is a precise description of the computation.

ENV COMONAD W: Type → Type, defined as W(A) = (StoreState, A):
  - extract : W(A) → A = snd (project out the value, discard store state)
  - extend : (W(A) → B) → W(A) → W(B) = λf. λ(s, a). (s, f(s, a))
  - duplicate : W(A) → W(W(A)) = λ(s, a). (s, (s, a))

COMONAD LAWS (must hold):
  L1: extract ∘ duplicate = id
  L2: fmap extract ∘ duplicate = id
  L3: duplicate ∘ duplicate = fmap duplicate ∘ duplicate

IN RUST (not Haskell — we implement the PATTERN, not the typeclass):
  pub struct Guided<A> {
      pub store_state: StoreSnapshot,  // the comonadic context
      pub value: A,                     // the carried value
  }

  impl<A> Guided<A> {
      pub fn extract(self) -> A { self.value }
      pub fn extend<B>(self, f: impl Fn(&Guided<A>) -> B) -> Guided<B> {
          let b = f(&self);
          Guided { store_state: self.store_state, value: b }
      }
  }

  // Usage: every CLI response is Guided<FormattedOutput>
  // The guidance footer is assembled by extend()ing the output with store-aware advice.

THIS IS Stage 1+ (ADR-GUIDANCE-001). At Stage 0, guidance is injected procedurally.
The comonadic structure is the FORMAL MODEL that Stage 0's procedural injection approximates.

V:PROP — extract(extend(f, wa)) == f(wa) (left identity)
V:PROP — extend(extract, wa) == wa (right identity)

