# TokenCounter Trait (guide/09-interface.md, guide/06-seed.md)

## Task
Implement the TokenCounter trait for budget management across SEED and INTERFACE namespaces.

## TokenCounter Trait
```rust
pub trait TokenCounter {
    fn count_tokens(&self, text: &str) -> usize;
    fn estimate_datom_tokens(&self, datom: &Datom) -> usize;
    fn estimate_seed_tokens(&self, seed: &SeedOutput) -> usize;
}
```

## Stage 0 Implementation: ApproxTokenCounter
```rust
pub struct ApproxTokenCounter;

impl TokenCounter for ApproxTokenCounter {
    fn count_tokens(&self, text: &str) -> usize {
        text.len() / 4  // chars/4 approximation (zero-dependency)
    }

    fn estimate_datom_tokens(&self, datom: &Datom) -> usize {
        // EDN canonical form length / 4
        let edn = canonical_edn::serialize_datom(datom);
        edn.len() / 4
    }

    fn estimate_seed_tokens(&self, seed: &SeedOutput) -> usize {
        self.count_tokens(&seed.orientation)
            + seed.constraints.iter().map(|c| self.count_tokens(&c.summary)).sum::<usize>()
            + seed.state.iter().map(|d| self.estimate_datom_tokens(d)).sum::<usize>()
            + seed.warnings.iter().map(|w| self.count_tokens(&w.message)).sum::<usize>()
            + self.count_tokens(&seed.directive)
    }
}
```

## Usage in SEED Pipeline
COMPRESS stage uses TokenCounter to iteratively reduce seed until it fits within k* budget.
ASSEMBLE stage uses it to estimate token cost of each projection level.

## Usage in INTERFACE
GuidanceFooter constrained to ~50 tokens.
ToolResponse metadata includes token_estimate for the full response.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] TokenCounter trait defined with 3 methods
- [ ] ApproxTokenCounter implements chars/4 (zero dependencies)
- [ ] SEED COMPRESS uses TokenCounter for budget compliance
- [ ] INTERFACE uses TokenCounter for footer sizing
- [ ] proptest: count_tokens monotonic in string length

## Traces To
guide/06-seed.md §6.2, guide/09-interface.md §9.2, INV-SEED-004

# Store Accessor Methods (guide/01-store.md §1.2)

## Task
Implement the essential read accessors on Store that all downstream namespaces depend on.

## Required Accessors
```rust
impl Store {
    // Core accessors
    pub fn len(&self) -> usize;              // total datom count
    pub fn is_empty(&self) -> bool;
    pub fn contains(&self, datom: &Datom) -> bool;
    pub fn datoms(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = &Datom>;

    // Transaction accessors
    pub fn transactions(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = TxId>;
    pub fn tx_datoms(&self, tx: &TxId) -> impl Iterator<Item = &Datom>;

    // Entity accessors
    pub fn entity(&self, id: &EntityId) -> impl Iterator<Item = &Datom>;
    pub fn datoms_for(&self, entity: EntityId, attr: &Attribute) -> Vec<&Datom>;

    // Frontier
    pub fn frontier(&self) -> &HashMap<AgentId, TxId>;

    // Schema
    pub fn schema(&self) -> &Schema;
}
```

## Index-Backed Queries
These accessors are backed by the four indexes:
- EAVT: entity queries → entity(), datoms_for()
- AEVT: attribute queries → all datoms with given attribute
- VAET: reverse lookup → entities with given value
- AVET: unique lookup → entity with given attribute+value

## Immutability Guarantee
All accessors return borrowed references (&). No mutable accessor exists on Store.
This is a direct consequence of C1 (append-only): the only mutation is transact(),
which returns a new Store or mutates via &mut self (internal only).

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All listed accessors implemented
- [ ] Index-backed for O(log n) or O(1) lookup
- [ ] No mutable accessors on Store
- [ ] Used by RESOLUTION, QUERY, HARVEST, SEED, GUIDANCE
- [ ] proptest: len() == datoms().count()
- [ ] proptest: contains() iff datoms() includes it

## Traces To
guide/01-store.md §1.2, guide/types.md Store section

