# 12 Typestate Encoding Patterns (spec/16-verification.md §16.3)

## Task
Define and implement the 12 typestate encoding patterns that provide V:TYPE compile-time verification.

## 12 Patterns (from spec/16-verification.md)
1. Transaction lifecycle: Building → Committed → Applied (PhantomData<S>)
2. Store initialization: Uninitialized → Genesis → Ready
3. Schema registration: Pending → Validated → Active
4. Query compilation: Parsed → Classified → Planned → Executable
5. Harvest pipeline: Detecting → Filtering → Asserting → Complete
6. Seed assembly: Associating → Assembling → Compressing → Emitting
7. Merge protocol: Receiving → Validating → Applying → Cascading
8. Guidance state: Inactive → Monitoring → Injecting
9. Layout initialization: Empty → Structured → Verified
10. Resolution routing: Detecting → Classifying → Routing → Resolved
11. Interface response: Building → Formatted → WithGuidance → Emitted
12. Trilateral projection: Computing → Classifying → Diverging → Reporting

## Typestate Pattern (Rust encoding)
```rust
// Sealed trait pattern
mod sealed { pub trait Sealed {} }

pub trait TxState: sealed::Sealed {}
pub struct Building;
pub struct Committed;
pub struct Applied;

impl sealed::Sealed for Building {}
impl sealed::Sealed for Committed {}
impl sealed::Sealed for Applied {}
impl TxState for Building {}
impl TxState for Committed {}
impl TxState for Applied {}

pub struct Transaction<S: TxState> {
    datoms: Vec<Datom>,
    _state: PhantomData<S>,
}

// State transitions are methods that consume self and return new type
impl Transaction<Building> {
    pub fn commit(self) -> Transaction<Committed> { ... }
}
impl Transaction<Committed> {
    pub fn apply(self, store: &mut Store) -> Transaction<Applied> { ... }
}
```

## V:TYPE Verification
Each typestate pattern is verified AT COMPILE TIME:
- Cannot call .apply() on Transaction<Building> — won't compile
- Cannot construct Transaction<Applied> without going through Building → Committed → Applied
- The sealed trait prevents external implementations

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All 12 typestate patterns defined with sealed traits
- [ ] Compile-time verification: invalid state transitions don't compile
- [ ] Each pattern used in its respective namespace
- [ ] Negative compilation tests (trybuild) for invalid transitions
- [ ] Documentation of each pattern in types.md

## Traces To
spec/16-verification.md §16.3, guide/types.md, guide/10-verification.md
